  "instructions": [
    "Combine rice flour and water in a mixing bowl to create a dough.",
    "Knead the dough for 10 minutes until it becomes smooth and elastic.",
    "Divide the dough into small balls, about 1 tablespoon each.",
    "Flatten each ball slightly into an oval shape.",
    "Heat a non-stick skillet or grill over medium-high heat.",
    "Add a small amount of vegetable oil to the skillet or grill.",
    "Cook the nem nuong for 2-3 minutes on each side, or until they are golden brown and slightly charred.",
    "Serve the nem nuong hot with nuka-zuke and a drizzle of fermented bean paste, fish sauce, sesame oil, salt, and black pepper.",
    "Garnish with mitsuba and additional nuka-zuke if desired."
  ],
